<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 8:23AM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Crawford, northwestern Barton and southwestern Vernon Counties
through 900 AM CDT...
At 822 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Arcadia, or 14 miles southeast of Fort Scott, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sheldon...                        Arcadia...
Bronaugh...                       Moundville...
Milo...                           Oskaloosa...
Hannon...
This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 77 and 85.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
